# ToDo App Build Plan

Goal:
Build a modular ToDo app with auth for the AFS x Reboot Tech Challenge.

Stack:
- Frontend: React + Vite
- Backend: Go
- Database: PostgreSQL official Docker image
- Auth: username/password, bcrypt, JWT
- API: REST
- Deployment: Docker Compose

Must deliver:
- Register and login
- JWT-protected ToDo CRUD
- User-specific ToDos
- Separate frontend, backend, and database containers
- README with setup, architecture, auth, and database notes


============================================================
1. File Structure
============================================================

ToDo-application/
  README.md
  docker-compose.yml
  .env.example
  .gitignore

  frontend/
    Dockerfile
    package.json
    index.html
    vite.config.js
    src/
      main.jsx
      App.jsx
      api.js
      styles.css
      components/
        AuthForm.jsx
        TodoForm.jsx
        TodoList.jsx
        TodoItem.jsx

  backend/
    Dockerfile
    go.mod
    go.sum
    main.go
    src/
      config/config.go
      db/db.go
      auth/password.go
      auth/jwt.go
      middleware/auth.go
      handlers/health.go
      handlers/auth.go
      handlers/todos.go
