Backend structure note:
- Keep main.go directly under backend/ for a small submission.
- Keep backend app packages under backend/src/ to mirror frontend/src/.
- Skip cmd/ and internal/ unless the backend grows larger.


============================================================
2. Environment
============================================================

.env.example should include:
- POSTGRES_DB=todo_app
- POSTGRES_USER=todo_user
- POSTGRES_PASSWORD=todo_password
- DATABASE_URL=postgres://todo_user:todo_password@postgres:5432/todo_app
- JWT_SECRET=replace_with_long_random_secret
- FRONTEND_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000
- VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000


============================================================
3. Database Schema
============================================================

users:
- id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY
- username VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE NOT NULL
- password_hash TEXT NOT NULL
- created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP

todos:
- id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY
- user_id INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
- title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
- completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE
- created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP

Rules:
- Never store plain text passwords.
- Never return password_hash.
- Every todo belongs to one user.
- Every todo query filters by user_id.

Final SQL:
CREATE TABLE users (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  password_hash TEXT NOT NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE todos (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);


============================================================
4. API Contract
============================================================

Public:
- GET /health
- POST /auth/register
- POST /auth/login

Protected:
- GET /auth/me
- GET /todos
- POST /todos
- PUT /todos/:id
- DELETE /todos/:id

Register/login body:
{
  "username": "mahmood",
  "password": "password123"
}

Register/login response:
{
  "token": "...",
  "user": { "id": 1, "username": "mahmood" }
}

Protected request header:
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

Create todo body:
{
  "title": "Finish project"
}

Update todo body:
{
  "title": "Finish project",
  "completed": true
}


============================================================
5. Docker Notes
============================================================

- postgres uses image postgres:16.
- Do not create a custom PostgreSQL Dockerfile.
- Mount ./db/init for first-run schema setup.
- Backend runs on port 5000.
- Frontend runs on port 3000.
- Backend DATABASE_URL uses host postgres, not localhost.
- Use docker compose down -v only to reset the database.
- Key commands: docker compose config, docker compose up --build, docker compose down.


============================================================
6. Build Plan
============================================================

Phase 1: Skeleton and Docker, 1.5 hours
- Create folders.
- Add docker-compose.yml.
- Add db/init/001_schema.sql.
- Add backend and frontend Dockerfiles.
- Add .env.example and .gitignore.
- Run docker compose config.

Phase 2: Go Backend Base, 1.5 hours
- Run go mod init todo-backend.
- Add dependencies:
  - github.com/jackc/pgx/v5/pgxpool
  - golang.org/x/crypto/bcrypt
  - github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5
- Optional router: github.com/gin-gonic/gin
- Build main.go.
- Connect PostgreSQL.
- Add CORS for http://localhost:3000.
- Add GET /health.

Phase 3: Auth Backend, 2 hours
- Implement bcrypt helpers.
- Implement JWT helpers.
- POST /auth/register:
  - validate username/password
  - hash password
  - insert user
  - return token + safe user
- POST /auth/login:
  - find user
  - compare password
  - return token + safe user
- GET /auth/me:
  - validate JWT
  - return current user

Phase 4: Todo Backend, 2 hours
- Implement JWT middleware.
- Protect all /todos routes.
- GET /todos: current user's todos only.
- POST /todos: create for current user.
- PUT /todos/:id: update current user's todo only.
- DELETE /todos/:id: delete current user's todo only.
- Return 404 for missing or unauthorized todo.

Phase 5: Frontend Base, 1 hour
- Create React/Vite app.
- Build api.js helper.
- Store token in localStorage.
- Load token on refresh.
- Call /auth/me if token exists.
- Keep App.jsx simple.

Phase 6: Frontend Auth, 1.5 hours
- Create AuthForm.jsx.
- Toggle login/register mode.
- Fields: username, password.
- Submit to /auth/register or /auth/login.
- Save token and user on success.
- Show clear error on failure.
- Add logout.

Phase 7: Frontend Todos, 2 hours
- Create TodoForm.jsx.
- Create TodoList.jsx.
- Create TodoItem.jsx.
- Implement fetch/create/update/delete.
- Add completed checkbox.
- Use prompt() for editing if time is tight.

Phase 8: Full Docker Test, 1 hour
- Run docker compose up --build.
- Open http://localhost:3000.
- Check http://localhost:5000/health.
- Register, create, complete, edit, delete.
- Refresh and confirm data persists.
- Logout and login again.

Phase 9: README, 1 hour
- Overview
- Tech stack
- Architecture
- Auth approach
- Database schema
- Run command
- URLs
- API endpoints


============================================================
7. Security Checklist
============================================================

- Passwords hashed with bcrypt.
- JWT secret from environment.
- password_hash never returned.
- Todo routes require Authorization: Bearer TOKEN.
- Every todo query filters by user_id.
- Invalid login returns generic error.
- Duplicate username returns clean error.
- .env is not committed.
- .env.example uses fake values.


============================================================
8. If Time Gets Tight
============================================================

Must keep:
- Docker Compose
- PostgreSQL official image
- Go backend
- Register/login
- JWT route protection
- Todo CRUD
- Frontend auth UI
- Frontend todo UI
- README

Can simplify:
- Basic CSS
- One App.jsx
- prompt() for editing
- No email field
- No refresh tokens
- No password reset
- No tests
- No advanced migrations


============================================================
9. Final Manual Test
============================================================

1. docker compose down -v
2. docker compose up --build
3. Open http://localhost:3000
4. Register a user.
5. Create two todos.
6. Complete one todo.
7. Edit one todo.
8. Delete one todo.
9. Refresh browser.
10. Confirm remaining todo exists.
11. Logout.
12. Login again.
13. Confirm user-specific data loads.
14. docker compose down

If all steps pass, submit the repository.


============================================================
10. Before Frontend Work
============================================================

Do these before starting the frontend if time allows. They are small backend
polish items that make the API/schema cleaner before the UI depends on it.

- DONE: Add updated_at to todos:
  - schema: updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
  - update query: SET updated_at = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
  - response model: UpdatedAt time.Time `json:"updated_at"`
  - tests: assert update response includes updated_at
- DONE: Add CREATE INDEX idx_todos_user_id ON todos(user_id).
- DONE: Replace duplicate-key string matching with pgconn.PgError code 23505.
- Change backend Dockerfile from go run . to go build + CMD ./server.
- DONE: Remove real JWT secret fallback from main.go.

Frontend impact:
- updated_at adds a new response field, but the frontend can ignore it.
- DB index, Dockerfile, JWT fallback, and duplicate-key handling do not change
  the frontend API contract.


============================================================
11. Future Improvements
============================================================

These can be done after the frontend if time allows. They should not affect
frontend work as long as API routes and response shapes stay the same.

Backend polish:
- Align go.mod Go version with the actual installed/stable Go version.
- Convert UserFromRequest helper into real auth middleware.
- Consider renaming backend/src to backend/internal for idiomatic Go.
- Add errorJSON helper to reduce repeated error response code.
- Consider moving SQL queries into a store/repository layer if handlers grow.

Frontend impact:
- Dockerfile, Go version, DB index, duplicate-key handling, and error helper
  should not affect the frontend.
- Real auth middleware should not affect the frontend if endpoints still require
  Authorization: Bearer TOKEN and return the same JSON.
- Repository/store refactor should not affect the frontend if response shapes
  stay unchanged.
